{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Fig. 43, the video is processed as RGB and the optical stream is used as input.",
    "The first branch, CA, was designed to model the relationship between action and foreground.",
    "Its effect is similar to that of noise contrast estimation (NCE) (Oord et al. 2018; Gutmann and Hyvärinen 2010), which maximizes the lower limit of mutual information (MI) between foreground features and real ground action features, thus achieving better foreground-background separation.",
    "The second branch, CW, introduces an independent attention mechanism that models the reverse foreground-to-action relationship to complement the first branch and establish foreground action consistency.",
    "In addition, it is able to learn semantically meaningful foreground features."
  ]
}